<inglise> Council Regulation (EC, ECSC, Euratom) No 2804/2000 of 18 December 2000 adjusting with effect from 1 July 2000 the remuneration and pensions of officials and other servants of the European Communities and the weightings applied thereto </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;, EST&Uuml;, EURATOM) nr 2804/2000, millega kohandatakse alates 1. juulist 2000 Euroopa &uuml;henduste ametnike ja muude teenistujate t&ouml;&ouml;tasusid ja pensione ning nende suhtes kohaldatavaid paranduskoefitsiente 18. detsember 2000 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN UNION, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA LIIDU N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Protocol on the Privileges and Immunities of the European Communities, and in particular Article 13 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &uuml;henduste privileegide ja immuniteetide protokolli, eriti selle artiklit 13, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Staff Regulations of Officials and the Conditions of Employment of Other Servants of the European Communities laid down by Regulation (EEC, Euratom, ECSC) No 259/68(1), as last amended by Regulation (EC, ECSC, Euratom) No 628/2000(2), and in particular Articles 63, 64, 65, 65a and 82 of the Staff Regulations, Annex XI to the said Staff Regulations, and Article 20, first paragraph, and Article 64 of the Conditions of Employment, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &uuml;henduste ametnike personalieeskirju ja nende &uuml;henduste muude teenistujate teenistustingimusi, mis on s&auml;testatud m&auml;&auml;ruses (EM&Uuml;, EURATOM, EST&Uuml;) nr 259/68, (1) viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;, EST&Uuml;, EURATOM) nr 628/2000, (2) eelk&otilde;ige personalieeskirjade artikleid 63, 64, 65, 65a ja 82, nende XI lisa ning teenistustingimuste artikli 20 esimest l&otilde;iku ja artiklit 64, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas: </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> (1) A review of the remuneration of Officials and Other Servants carried out on the basis of a report by the Commission has shown that the remuneration and pensions of officials and other servants of the Communities should be adjusted under the 2000 annual review. </inglise>
<eesti> 1) komisjoni aruande alusel toimunud ametnike ja muude teenistujate t&ouml;&ouml;tasude &uuml;mberhindamisel on selgunud, et 2000. aasta &uuml;mberhindamise k&auml;igus tuleks &uuml;henduse ametnike ja muude teenistujate t&ouml;&ouml;tasusid ja pensione kohandada; </eesti>
<inglise> (2) The annual adjustment in respect of 2001 may entail the establishment before 31 December 2001 of new weightings with retroactive effect from 1 July 2001. </inglise>
<eesti> 2) 2001. aastal toimuva iga-aastase kohandamise k&auml;igus v&otilde;ib enne 31. detsembrit 2001 kindlaks m&auml;&auml;rata uued paranduskoefitsiendid, mida kohaldatakse tagasiulatuvalt alates 1. juulist 2001; </eesti>
<inglise> (3) These new weightings could lead to retroactive adjustments to remuneration and pensions (positive or negative) in respect of the period of 2001 for which payments have already been made on the basis of this Regulation. </inglise>
<eesti> 3) uute paranduskoefitsientidega v&otilde;ivad kaasneda tagasiulatuvad (positiivsed v&otilde;i negatiivsed) kohandused 2001. aasta selle ajavahemiku t&ouml;&ouml;tasudes ja pensionides, mille eest v&auml;ljamaksed on k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse alusel juba tehtud; </eesti>
<inglise> (4) Provisions should therefore be made for the payment of arrears in the event of an upward adjustment as a result of these weightings or for the recovery of sums overpaid in the event of a downward adjustment for the period between the effective date and the date of entry into force of the Council's decision on the annual adjustment in respect of 2001. </inglise>
<eesti> 4) seep&auml;rast tuleks ette n&auml;ha, et 2001. aastal tehtavaid iga-aastaseid kohandusi k&auml;sitleva n&otilde;ukogu otsuse kohaldamise algkuup&auml;eva ja j&otilde;ustumise kuup&auml;eva vahelises ajavahemikus tuleb paranduskoefitsientidest tulenevate positiivsete kohanduste puhul maksta need summad tagantj&auml;rele ning negatiivsete kohanduste puhul enammakstud summad tagasi maksta; </eesti>
<inglise> (5) Provision should be made for the effects of any such recovery to be spread over a period of not more than twelve months following the date of entry into force of the Council's decision on the annual adjustment in respect of 2001. </inglise>
<eesti> 5) tuleks ette n&auml;ha, et iga sellise tagasimakse m&otilde;ju jaotatakse maksimaalselt kaheteistk&uuml;mne kuu peale, mis j&auml;rgnevad 2001. aastal tehtavaid iga-aastaseid kohandusi k&auml;sitleva n&otilde;ukogu otsuse j&otilde;ustumisele; </eesti>
<inglise> (6) Greece will adopt the euro from 1 January 2001 with a conversion rate of EUR 1 = GDR 340,750, </inglise>
<eesti> 6) Kreeka v&otilde;tab alates 1. jaanuarist 2001 kasutusele euro &uuml;mberarvestuskursiga 1 euro = 340,750 GDR, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
